Express.js: It's a popular Node.js web application framework for building web apps and APIs quickly.
Middleware: Functions that handle requests, have access to request and response objects, and can pass control to the next middleware with next().
next(): Callback to pass control to the next middleware in the stack.
res.send(): Sends a response to the client. Sets appropriate Content-Type header based on data type.
app.listen(3000): Starts a server listening on port 3000
